Population statistics-related scripts are kept here. 
All scripts are configured for use with the North Carolina State University Bioinformatics Research Center Cluster, which makes use of the SLURM job scheduler.

All scripts require pixy (available at: https://pixy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html)
I installed pixy on the BRC as a dedicated conda environment: conda create -n pixy_env -conda-forge pixy
Other installation methods are available and are described within pixy documentation

All population statistics generation scripts make use of:
  1) The all-sites VCF file (all_samples.allsites.vcf.gz)
  2) A user-specified window size for a specific population statistic to be calculated for
  3) A user-specified output directory
  4) User-specified threads count
  5) The pathway to the alignment files as generated by D.H. (needed to generate populations companion file required by pixy)
    NOTE: pixy does not use alignment data. I simply took advantage of that directory's architecture to associate population names with sample IDs
    NOTE: if the user does not have access to that directory, they can comment out the entire for loop and just use the populations.txt file here
